<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,266,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,317,549,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Nogueira" authorityName="Santos &amp; Nogueira" box="[333,753,549,575]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neblina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[333,521,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Architis neblina</emphasis>
Santos &amp; Nogueira
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[761,855,549,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[761,855,549,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[988,1184,550,575]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ikuruwa">
<emphasis box="[988,1184,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Architis ikuruwa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1333,550,575]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comaina">
<emphasis box="[1199,1333,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">A. comaina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altamira">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">A. altamira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos" authorityName="Santos" box="[265,478,589,615]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catuaba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[265,392,590,615]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">A. catuaba</emphasis>
Santos
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[486,581,589,615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[486,581,589,615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the presence of long copulatory ducts which are enclosed in epigynal integument folds. It can be distinguished from these species by a small anterior subtriangular projection over MF in the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[410,481,669,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[186,1421,240,1675]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,194,1690]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Architis spp. 7 – 8, Architis neblina Santos &amp; Nogueira sp. nov. (paratype IBSP 91474): 7, female epigynum, ventral view; 8, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. 9 – 10, Architis capricorna Carico (IBSP 94871): 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, male pedipalpus, ventral-retrolateral view. The arrow points to a hyaline area at the retrolateral-posterior border of the cymbial alveolus. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; dRTA, dorsal branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; DTP, distal tegular projection; FD, fertilisation ducts; HS, head of spermathecae; LL, lateral lobes of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field of epigynum; RP, retrolateral projection of VTA; SC, sclerotised case of CD; SK, spermathecal knob; SS, stalk of spermathecae; ST, subtegulum; vRTA, ventral branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 7 – 9, 0.1 mm; 10, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182891/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[466,481,669,695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) and by the posterior fourth of the copulatory ducts, which are inside sclerotised cases (
<figureCitation box="[228,299,709,735]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[186,1421,240,1675]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,194,1690]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Architis spp. 7 – 8, Architis neblina Santos &amp; Nogueira sp. nov. (paratype IBSP 91474): 7, female epigynum, ventral view; 8, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. 9 – 10, Architis capricorna Carico (IBSP 94871): 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, male pedipalpus, ventral-retrolateral view. The arrow points to a hyaline area at the retrolateral-posterior border of the cymbial alveolus. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; dRTA, dorsal branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; DTP, distal tegular projection; FD, fertilisation ducts; HS, head of spermathecae; LL, lateral lobes of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field of epigynum; RP, retrolateral projection of VTA; SC, sclerotised case of CD; SK, spermathecal knob; SS, stalk of spermathecae; ST, subtegulum; vRTA, ventral branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 7 – 9, 0.1 mm; 10, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182891/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[283,299,709,735]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
