<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,266,1695]" box="[197,559,749,775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,427,749,775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,266,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,288,789,815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Female</emphasis>
(based on 
<typeStatus box="[415,518,789,815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
from São Gabriel da Cachoeira, 
<collectingCountry box="[903,980,789,815]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). Carapace reddish-brown, pilose, with a median and a pair of light green lateral stripes. Anterior eye row strongly procurved, with lateral eyes larger than median eyes. Posterior eyes with approximately the same diameter as anterior laterals. Thoracic sulcus conspicuous. Clypeus cream-coloured, with lateral red-brown bands under lateral anterior eyes. Chelicerae yellow, suffused with dark grey. Labium and endites reddish-brown. Sternum cream-coloured, with four radial dark-grey stripes on each side. Pedipalpus cream-coloured, with dark-grey rings apically on each segment from femur to tarsus and basally on tibia and tarsus. Leg coxa and trochanter cream-coloured, remaining segments reddish-brown with pale rings basally, medially and apically on femur, tibia, metatarsus and tarsus. Abdomen dorsally reddish-brown, dark-grey in posterior third, with scattered cream-coloured stripes. Laterally dark grey, with longitudinal scattered cream-coloured stripes. Venter dark grey, suffused with creamcoloured spots on anterior half and with a pair of marginal cream-coloured stripes. Anterior lateral spinnerets reddish-brown, remaining spinnerets black. Total length 
<number box="[811,851,1229,1255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="4.3">4.3</number>
. Carapace 
<number box="[977,1013,1229,1255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="1.8">1.8</number>
long, 
<number box="[1087,1124,1229,1255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="1.6">1.6</number>
wide. Tibia I length 
<number box="[1366,1405,1229,1255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="3.2">3.2</number>
, II 
<number box="[151,191,1269,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="3.2">3.2</number>
, III 
<number box="[237,277,1269,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="2.6">2.6</number>
, IV 3.0. Abdomen 
<number box="[499,535,1269,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="2.4">2.4</number>
long, 
<number box="[608,645,1269,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="1.2">1.2</number>
wide. Epigynum with long median field and projecting beyond epigastric sulcus (
<figureCitation box="[325,396,1309,1335]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[186,1421,240,1675]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,194,1690]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Architis spp. 7 – 8, Architis neblina Santos &amp; Nogueira sp. nov. (paratype IBSP 91474): 7, female epigynum, ventral view; 8, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. 9 – 10, Architis capricorna Carico (IBSP 94871): 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, male pedipalpus, ventral-retrolateral view. The arrow points to a hyaline area at the retrolateral-posterior border of the cymbial alveolus. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; dRTA, dorsal branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; DTP, distal tegular projection; FD, fertilisation ducts; HS, head of spermathecae; LL, lateral lobes of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field of epigynum; RP, retrolateral projection of VTA; SC, sclerotised case of CD; SK, spermathecal knob; SS, stalk of spermathecae; ST, subtegulum; vRTA, ventral branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 7 – 9, 0.1 mm; 10, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182891/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[379,396,1309,1335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Posterior fourth of copulatory ducts encapsulated inside bilobed sclerotised cases. Base of spermathecae indistinct, stalk of spermathecae short and wide. Head of spermathecae with an irregular, bilobed spermathecal knob. Fertilisation ducts mesal, connected to the stalk of spermathecae and curved ectally (
<figureCitation box="[245,316,1429,1455]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[186,1421,240,1675]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,194,1690]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Architis spp. 7 – 8, Architis neblina Santos &amp; Nogueira sp. nov. (paratype IBSP 91474): 7, female epigynum, ventral view; 8, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. 9 – 10, Architis capricorna Carico (IBSP 94871): 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, male pedipalpus, ventral-retrolateral view. The arrow points to a hyaline area at the retrolateral-posterior border of the cymbial alveolus. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; dRTA, dorsal branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; DTP, distal tegular projection; FD, fertilisation ducts; HS, head of spermathecae; LL, lateral lobes of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field of epigynum; RP, retrolateral projection of VTA; SC, sclerotised case of CD; SK, spermathecal knob; SS, stalk of spermathecae; ST, subtegulum; vRTA, ventral branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 7 – 9, 0.1 mm; 10, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182891/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[300,316,1429,1455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,266,1695]" box="[197,947,1469,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
