<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,266,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,389,1509,1535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Natural history</emphasis>
. All the specimens were collected at night in a mature dryland forest by visual search as part of a study on the variation in spider species richness along an altitudinal gradient at the Pico da 
<taxonomicName box="[1336,1432,1549,1575]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neblina">Neblina</taxonomicName>
, the highest Brazilian mountain. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Nogueira" authorityName="Santos &amp; Nogueira" box="[740,1093,1589,1615]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neblina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[740,861,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">A. neblina</emphasis>
Santos &amp; Nogueira
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1194,1589,1615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1101,1194,1589,1615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
occurred only at the lower level of the altitudinal gradient, approximately 
<quantity box="[777,851,1629,1655]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
